would have been buttoned on the wrong side and the shutter release on the Leica 
would have been on the wrong side of the camera. 
</P>
<P>
Cameras seem to have been designed for righties, not lefties. 
</P>
<P>
(Nothing abnormal about using the left eye in looking through the view-finder. 
I am right-handed and right-footed . . . but I have probably taken as many 
pictures left-eyed as right-eyed. It just doesn't make any difference. 
</P>
<P>
