<HEADLINE>
<P>
ALLA BREVE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JOHN HENKEN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROREM: "A QUAKER READER," "VIEWS FROM THE OLDEST HOUSE." Catherine Crozier, 
organ. 
</P>
<P>
Delos D/CD 3076(compact disc). These two suites of pictorial miniatures hold a 
wide range of colors and impressions, presented in a tonal language both 
sophisticated and accessible. "A Quaker Reader," with its evocations of martyrs 
and ecstasies, is the more flamboyant, but both offer grateful and 
demonstrative work to the performer. Crozier plays them with clarity and 
passion, on the Marcussen organ at Wichita State University. JOHN HENKEN 
