<HEADLINE>
<P>
ITALY PASSES LAW THAT TARGETS MAFIA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ROME 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Italy's parliament has passed a new law aimed at stepping up the battle against 
the sophisticated, modern Mafia, especially the laundering of its profits into 
legal businesses. 
</P>
<P>
The new law gives police and magistrates greater powers to investigate the 
finances and property of Mafia suspects and to seize profits from crime. 
</P>
