<HEADLINE>
<P>
POLICE OVERKILL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The San Diego Police Department is understaffed? They claim that a response 
time of 30 minutes or longer is very common, yet they send 30 cars, motorcycle 
units and a helicopter to corral 200 secondary students conducting an orderly 
protest. Can this be the same understaffed force? 
</P>
<P>
This overreaction should be an embarrassment to the SDPD and the citizens of 
San Diego. 
</P>
<P>
JIM WRIGHT 
</P>
<P>
San Diego 
</P>
