<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNINGSIDE HAS A POSITIVE SIDE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I am a very concerned freshman who attends Morningside High School in 
Inglewood. 
</P>
<P>
Although I did not participate in the protest, I feel very frustrated that the 
media has brought primarily negative attention to our school. 
</P>
<P>
I understand that our school has many problems. They shouldn't be ignored, but 
the media makes it seem that Morningside is so bad that students fear walking 
from class to class. I'm sure Los Angeles Times readers think bad things about 
us. The school has many positive points too. 
</P>
<P>
Many parents may have considered sending their children to Morningside. 
However, I'm sure they've lost interest now. Please present both sides of the 
picture in further newspaper articles about our school. 
</P>
<P>
TANISHA BAISLEY 
</P>
<P>
Inglewood 
</P>
</TEXT>
