BUTTERFLY BANTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Ree Strange Sheck's article on the Costa Rica rain forest ("Alone With Nature 
in a Tropic Rain Forest," Feb. 11) has me bemused and confused. In discussing 
plant mimicry, the writer described a passion flower that had leaves with 
Velcro-like hairs "to catch marauding butterfly larvae." Pray, how does a larva 
maraud? I thought they tended to be on the sedentary side. 
</P>
<P>
SARA MERIC 
