<HEADLINE>
<P>
EDUCATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I can't believe how shortsighted everyone -- young and old, rich and poor -- is 
on the subject of education. 
</P>
<P>
No one seems to realize that no matter if children are black, brown, yellow or 
white, they are the future of this nation -- our nation. A few children from 
private schools cannot run an entire nation. Maybe instead of worrying about 
who and how many, we need to concentrate on educating all as best as possible. 
After all, as I was told by my daughter's kindergarten teacher, the only fair 
is in Pomona. Let's stop worrying about "equality" and concentrate on "quality 
education." Maybe this approach will make for more equality. 
</P>
<P>
NANCY SCHWAB 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
