<HEADLINE>
<P>
TENNIS ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
MASUR TO FACE STICH IN MEMPHIS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Wally Masur put on a clinic for Glenn Layendecker Saturday night as the 
Australian won, 6-3, 6-2, to earn his way into the championship match of the 
$250,000 Volvo Indoor tennis tournament in Memphis, Tenn. 
</P>
<P>
Masur, seeded sixth, will meet unseeded Michael Stich, who eliminated Gary 
Muller, 7-5, 7-6 (7-4). 
</P>
<P>
Aaron Krickstein and Tim Mayotte both won their semifinal singles matches in 
straight sets to advance to today's final in the Eagle tournament at 
Scottsdale, Ariz. Krickstein beat Spain's Emilio Sanchez, 7-6 (7-5), 6-4, and 
Mayotte defeated Jim Grabb, 6-4, 6-1. 
</P>
<P>
Top-seeded Brad Gilbert of the United States beat Michael Tauson, 6-3, 6-3, and 
will face Jonas Svensson in the final at Rotterdam, the Netherlands. 
</P>
</TEXT>
