<HEADLINE>
<P>
GWYNN HAS QUICKEST TOP FUEL RUN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Special to The Times 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
BAYTOWN, Tex. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Top Fuel driver Darrell Gwynn recorded the quickest elapsed time in drag racing 
history Saturday during qualifying for the third-annual Fram Supernationals at 
Houston Raceway Park. 
</P>
<P>
Gwynn, of Miami, covered the quarter-mile distance in 4.909 seconds at 280.46 
m.p.h. in his dragster to surpass the mark of 4.919 set by Gary Ormsby last 
October at the Texas Motorplex in Dallas. 
</P>
<P>
Other qualifying leaders for today's final eliminations include John Force in 
Funny Car and Mark Pawuk in Pro Stock. 
</P>
<P>
Pawuk, of Richfield, Ohio, recorded the quickest run in NHRA Pro Stock history 
with a 7.220 at 188.36 in an Olds Cutlass, the first time that he has been the 
No. 1 qualifier. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
