<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTHERN SECTION BOYS 2-A BASKETBALL; 
</P>
<P>
CAVAZOS LEADS SANTA MARIA ST. JOSEPH TO VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIKE REILLEY, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Santa Maria St. Joseph won its first Southern Section 2-A boys' basketball 
championship Saturday at the free-throw line. 
</P>
<P>
Laguna Beach's free-throw line. 
</P>
<P>
Roger Cavazos scored 20 of his game-high 32 points in the second half as the 
Knights rallied from a 14-point deficit to beat Laguna Beach, 70-68, at the 
Sports Arena. 
</P>
<P>
The Knights opened the fourth quarter with a 15-2 run and Spencer MacCuish made 
the front end of a one-and-one free throw opportunity with five seconds left to 
seal the victory. 
</P>
<P>
Laguna Beach missed five free throws late in the game, including the front end 
of three one-and-ones in the final 1 minute 29 seconds. 
</P>
<P>
"I thought in the last two minutes the game was ours," Laguna Beach Coach Ed 
Bowen said. "All we had to do was win it at the free-throw line." 
</P>
<P>
Instead, St. Joseph, which lost four of its first six games, improved to 20-7. 
Laguna Beach is now 22-6. 
</P>
<P>
St. Joseph led, 69-67, after a free throw by Cavazo with 1:28 left. 
</P>
<P>
Borella, who scored 18 of his team-high 25 points in the first half, missed the 
front end of a one-and-one opportunity with 1:17 left to begin the Artists' 
struggle from the line. 
</P>
<P>
The Artists had made nine of 12 free throws before the fourth quarter, but made 
only seven of 14 in the final quarter. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Game Story 
</P>
