<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTH COUNTY NEED FOR ADDED DEPUTIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Orange County Board of Supervisors recently postponed the approval of more 
deputies for South Orange County. 
</P>
<P>
This area has had phenomenal growth in the past five years, while the number of 
deputies for the area has remained constant. 
</P>
<P>
The supervisors didn't hesitate to approve development in South Orange County, 
but now hesitate to allow residents in this area to have equal protection 
afforded to the area. 
</P>
<P>
One has to wonder if the county board is not a puppet of developers. Voters 
should remember this when the time comes to make changes. 
</P>
<P>
JAMES SOCHA 
</P>
<P>
Laguna Niguel 
</P>
</TEXT>
