<HEADLINE>
<P>
PENALTY FOR DOCTORS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In The Times (Feb. 22), there was a news item regarding a doctor in Anaheim who 
was suspended for 90 days and put on 10 years' probation by the State Board of 
Medical Quality Assurance for admittedly filing false workers' compensation 
claims. 
</P>
<P>
If the medical profession wishes to retain any respect for its so-called high 
ethics, then it's high time they took drastic steps in cases such as this, 
instead of the slap-on-the-wrist punishment they administer. 
</P>
<P>
Why not take away a license permanently? Perhaps to some this is a high price 
to pay, but it would show others that a license to practice medicine is not 
also a license to steal. 
</P>
<P>
JOHN HALL 
</P>
<P>
Garden Grove 
</P>
