<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY COLLEGE ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
RANCHO SANTIAGO BEATS OCC, 4-3, ON PINCH HIT IN EIGHTH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEVE KRESAL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
COSTA MESA 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
George Saldana's pinch-hit RBI single in the eighth inning gave Rancho Santiago 
College a 4-3 victory over Orange Coast in an Orange Empire Conference baseball 
game Saturday at OCC. 
</P>
<P>
Saldana's two-out single to right scored Jeff White, who had opened the inning 
with a single and went to second on a balk. 
</P>
<P>
OCC had two on and two outs in the ninth when reliever Rob Nay got pinch-hitter 
Mike Burns to ground out to end the game. It was Nay's first save. 
</P>
<P>
Rancho Santiago (14-2, 4-0) built a 3-1 lead with two runs in the fourth and 
Marty Neff's solo home run in the fifth. It was Neff's 10th home run of the 
season. 
</P>
<P>
OCC tied it with two runs in the seventh on an RBI triple by Sean Therien and 
an RBI single by Kevin Schula. 
</P>
<P>
Winning pitcher Matt Lackie (4-1) allowed six hits and had eight strikeouts. 
Loser Tom Irwin (3-1) allowed 11 hits in nine innings for OCC (8-8, 1-2). STEVE 
KRESAL 
</P>
</TEXT>
