<P>
HIGH SCHOOL BASEBALL; 
</P>
<P>
ORANGE GLEN WINS OPENER ON NO-HITTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Scott Coleman and Jim Roby combined to throw a no-hitter for Orange Glen, and 
Coleman had five runs-batted in as the Patriots defeated Mar Vista, 14-0, in a 
season-opening Warhawk Tournament game. 
</P>
<P>
Coleman hit a bases-loaded home run during Orange Glen's six-run first inning. 
</P>
<P>
He also struck out nine in four innings. 
</P>
<P>
"After the grand slam, his adrenaline was pumping the rest of the day," Orange 
Glen Coach Ken Walker said. "He was on top of things." 
</P>
<P>
In other Warhawk Tournament games: 
</P>
<P>
Serra 12, San Dieguito 9 -- Serra scored a total of 11 runs in the second and 
third innings, overcoming host San Dieguito's eight in the first two innings. 
</P>
<P>
Sean Kerr (1-0) came on in the third inning and didn't allow a hit in four 
innings of work for Serra (1-0). Murry Estabrook had two hits and three RBIs 
for Serra and Mike Miller and Justin Wible each had two hits and two RBIs. 
</P>
<P>
San Dieguito (0-1) scored four runs in the second on a three-base throwing 
error. 
</P>
<P>
"We really played some little league baseball and looked pretty silly in the 
second inning, but we tied them and went ahead," Serra Coach Ken Sovay said. 
</P>
<P>
Kearny 11, Bonita Vista 4 -- Eddie Feistel went three for three and Jason 
Redondo and Jermaine Matthews each had two hits for visiting Kearny. 
</P>
<P>
Castle Park 20, Valhalla 9 -- Jackie Sosa hit two home runs -- one in the first 
with two on and another in the fifth with one on -- for host Castle Park (1-0). 
</P>
<P>
Monte Vista 2, Madison 1 -- Robbie Stone (1-0) pitched a one-hitter and had 14 
strikeouts for host Monte Vista (1-0). 
</P>
<P>
Nonleague 
</P>
<P>
Grossmont 5-18, Calexico 3-2 -- Scott Brennan went six for six and had six 
RBIs, including a three-run home run, as host Grossmont (2-0) swept. 
