<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Guard Jeff Bregel of the San Francisco 49ers was arrested early Saturday and 
charged with being drunk in public, according to San Jose police. 
</P>
<P>
"He was standing on a corner with his shirt off and was challenging someone to 
a fight," police spokesman Mitch Fagan said. 
</P>
<P>
Bregel, 25, was the 49ers' second-round draft pick out of USC in 1987. 
</P>
</TEXT>
