<HEADLINE>
<P>
BIG WEST; 
</P>
<P>
SANTA BARBARA GETS 20-WIN SEASON, 77-76 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Gary Gray scored 20 points and Eric McArthur added 18 to lead UC Santa Barbara 
over San Jose State, 77-76, in a Big West Conference game Saturday night at San 
Jose. 
</P>
<P>
Carrick DeHart hit a 12-foot jump shot from the right baseline with 21 seconds 
remaining to give UC Santa Barbara a 77-73 lead and seal its third consecutive 
20-win season. 
</P>
<P>
The Gauchos improved to 20-7 in the conference and 13-5 overall. 
</P>
<P>
Troy Batiste of San Jose State (8-19 and 5-13) hit a three-point field goal at 
the buzzer, cutting the Gauchos margin of victory to 77-76. 
</P>
<P>
Trailing 58-55 with 9:10 remaining, McArthur and Gray sparked a 9-0 run that 
keyed the victory for UC Santa Barbara. 
</P>
<P>
McArthur, the NCAA Division I leading rebounder at 13.6 a game, threw down a 
thunderous dunk to start the run, and Gray -- with 14 points in the second half 
-- hit a hook shot on the baseline and scored on a offensive rebound after a 
missed free throw. 
</P>
<P>
Andre Brooks led San Jose State, who had four players in double figures, with 
16 points. 
</P>
</TEXT>
